Text.SourceString: Hello to you too! I’m <NPCName>Macy</>.//<portrait=normal>Where are you visiting from? It’s nice to finally have a tourist in town.
Text.LocalizedString: Hello to you too! I’m <NPCName>Macy</>.//<portrait=normal>Where are you visiting from? It’s nice to finally have a tourist in town.

Text.SourceString: Oh! You just moved to Coral Island?//<portrait=normal>That’s amazing, welcome, and confusing. Why? Well, I hope you’re getting around all right.//Coral Island is kind of big, so getting your bearings can be pretty hard at first.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! You just moved to Coral Island?//<portrait=normal>That’s amazing, welcome, and confusing. Why? Well, I hope you’re getting around all right.//Coral Island is kind of big, so getting your bearings can be pretty hard at first.

Text.SourceString: You’ll get used to it in no time. I have no doubt.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ll get used to it in no time. I have no doubt.

Text.SourceString: I took some pictures of the recycling center.//<portrait=happy>I want to document its stages and call the series The Mess We Caused.
Text.LocalizedString: I took some pictures of the recycling center.//<portrait=happy>I want to document its stages and call the series The Mess We Caused.

Text.SourceString: I have a picture of the recycling center when it was half empty, if you want to check it out.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a picture of the recycling center when it was half empty, if you want to check it out.

Text.SourceString: I saw you clearing up debris on the lot near <NPCName>Erika’s</> house last week, and I called out to you.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think you heard me, though. Unless…
Text.LocalizedString: I saw you clearing up debris on the lot near <NPCName>Erika’s</> house last week, and I called out to you.//<portrait=concerned>I don’t think you heard me, though. Unless…

Text.SourceString: Oh well. You seemed busy that day.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well. You seemed busy that day.

Text.SourceString: Living at the inn really limits the gardening I can do.//I'm itching to plant some cauliflower, okra, all that veggie stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Living at the inn really limits the gardening I can do.//I'm itching to plant some cauliflower, okra, all that veggie stuff.

Text.SourceString: Fruit though? Uh, you need way more room for that. Not sure I'm up for that level of commitment yet.
Text.LocalizedString: Fruit though? Uh, you need way more room for that. Not sure I'm up for that level of commitment yet.

Text.SourceString: What pics sell best? Oh, easy! People can't get enough of beach shots. Easiest cash I ever made!
Text.LocalizedString: What pics sell best? Oh, easy! People can't get enough of beach shots. Easiest cash I ever made!

Text.SourceString: I’m a sucker for nature panoramas. There’s always so much to take in! So much to share.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a sucker for nature panoramas. There’s always so much to take in! So much to share.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a morning person. According to a study I read years ago, my chronotype means that my most efficient work hours are after 11 am.//<portrait=normal>Feels right to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a morning person. According to a study I read years ago, my chronotype means that my most efficient work hours are after 11 am.//<portrait=normal>Feels right to me.

Text.SourceString: If I eat too much in the morning, I feel nauseated all day! So I just grab coffee and bread before I head out.
Text.LocalizedString: If I eat too much in the morning, I feel nauseated all day! So I just grab coffee and bread before I head out.

Text.SourceString: Give me a sec, just gathering my thoughts. What was I saying?
Text.LocalizedString: Give me a sec, just gathering my thoughts. What was I saying?

Text.SourceString: Stephen's pics are a hot commodity! He's a pro, always ready for his close-up!
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen's pics are a hot commodity! He's a pro, always ready for his close-up!

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Are you okay?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>? Are you okay?

Text.SourceString: You seem distraught. If there's something on your mind, just let it out.
Text.LocalizedString: You seem distraught. If there's something on your mind, just let it out.

Text.SourceString: I get bored quickly. I play video games when I’m tired of editing pictures.//<portrait=happy>Then, if I’m still bored, I watch other people playing video games.
Text.LocalizedString: I get bored quickly. I play video games when I’m tired of editing pictures.//<portrait=happy>Then, if I’m still bored, I watch other people playing video games.

Text.SourceString: Don't ask me why. I guess there's just something cool about watching other people game.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't ask me why. I guess there's just something cool about watching other people game.

Text.SourceString: There are a lot of picturesque spots here. Um…
Text.LocalizedString: There are a lot of picturesque spots here. Um…

Text.SourceString: So, here's the deal: I take the shots, then post 'em online to license. People buy the rights to use my pics through a third party.//<portrait=happy>This cool website I use for my photos.
Text.LocalizedString: So, here's the deal: I take the shots, then post 'em online to license. People buy the rights to use my pics through a third party.//<portrait=happy>This cool website I use for my photos.

Text.SourceString: Ever heard of Pletty Inc.?//<portrait=happy>Yeah, that’s the site that sells my pics.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever heard of Pletty Inc.?//<portrait=happy>Yeah, that’s the site that sells my pics.

Text.SourceString: I've got a whole portfolio of Stephen: Lobster, Cute Lobster, Lobster Day Out, Sea Life.//<portrait=normal>Umm, what else? What else?
Text.LocalizedString: I've got a whole portfolio of Stephen: Lobster, Cute Lobster, Lobster Day Out, Sea Life.//<portrait=normal>Umm, what else? What else?

Text.SourceString: I need to concentrate.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to concentrate.

Text.SourceString: Mind getting back to your thing, so I can get back to mine?
Text.LocalizedString: Mind getting back to your thing, so I can get back to mine?

Text.SourceString: You can try going to the library. Or meditation, maybe.
Text.LocalizedString: You can try going to the library. Or meditation, maybe.

Text.SourceString: I don’t like the rain. I usually spend rainy days editing pictures at the library and just play video games in my room all night.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like the rain. I usually spend rainy days editing pictures at the library and just play video games in my room all night.

Text.SourceString: Rain doesn’t seem to bother you, though, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Rain doesn’t seem to bother you, though, huh?

Text.SourceString: Stephen’s doing well today, thanks for asking.//<portrait=happy>How 'bout you, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen’s doing well today, thanks for asking.//<portrait=happy>How 'bout you, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Streaming games could be a blast!//<portrait=normal>Just not sure it's my thing. I'm not about being in the spotlight.
Text.LocalizedString: Streaming games could be a blast!//<portrait=normal>Just not sure it's my thing. I'm not about being in the spotlight.

Text.SourceString: If I ever get over that, maybe I'll give it a try.//<portrait=blushing>Who am I kidding?! I love the shadows WAY too much.
Text.LocalizedString: If I ever get over that, maybe I'll give it a try.//<portrait=blushing>Who am I kidding?! I love the shadows WAY too much.

Text.SourceString: Saturday evenings? I spend them at the Tavern.//I don’t have a set schedule during the week. I usually just let the camera take me wherever.
Text.LocalizedString: Saturday evenings? I spend them at the Tavern.//I don’t have a set schedule during the week. I usually just let the camera take me wherever.

Text.SourceString: I prefer to be behind the camera. Oh, don’t worry too much about me! I think I’m an okay-looking and interesting gal.//<portrait=happy>I just don’t like being photographed.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to be behind the camera. Oh, don’t worry too much about me! I think I’m an okay-looking and interesting gal.//<portrait=happy>I just don’t like being photographed.

Text.SourceString: The spotlight makes me nervous.
Text.LocalizedString: The spotlight makes me nervous.

Text.SourceString: I call my parents every week to let them know I’m still <Italic>alive</>.//<portrait=happy>No, really. If I didn't, they'd freak out. Masters of drama.//<portrait=blushing>Still love 'em, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I call my parents every week to let them know I’m still <Italic>alive</>.//<portrait=happy>No, really. If I didn't, they'd freak out. Masters of drama.//<portrait=blushing>Still love 'em, though.

Text.SourceString: I’m secretly relieved when friends cancel plans. Socializing is exhausting sometimes.//<portrait=normal>Keep it between us, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m secretly relieved when friends cancel plans. Socializing is exhausting sometimes.//<portrait=normal>Keep it between us, okay?

Text.SourceString: The mess is what’s making my room feel dirty. But in all seriousness, it really isn’t. I’d say it’s immaculate.
Text.LocalizedString: The mess is what’s making my room feel dirty. But in all seriousness, it really isn’t. I’d say it’s immaculate.

Text.SourceString: I scrub the floor with disinfectant. You could eat off it if you wanted to... Just, uh...don’t, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I scrub the floor with disinfectant. You could eat off it if you wanted to... Just, uh...don’t, though.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'm going overboard with all the scrubbing.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'm going overboard with all the scrubbing.

Text.SourceString: Do you think it’s because I’m covered in dirt a lot? I always have this icky feeling that my room never feels clean, you know?//So I just keep scrubbing and scrubbing. Not sure if I'm making sense here.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think it’s because I’m covered in dirt a lot? I always have this icky feeling that my room never feels clean, you know?//So I just keep scrubbing and scrubbing. Not sure if I'm making sense here.

Text.SourceString: Fave video game genre? Oh gosh, oh gosh! Tough call. But I'd have to say action-adventure games.//<portrait=happy>Heck yeah! Action-adventure all the way. I can just lose myself in a whole new world whenever I want.
Text.LocalizedString: Fave video game genre? Oh gosh, oh gosh! Tough call. But I'd have to say action-adventure games.//<portrait=happy>Heck yeah! Action-adventure all the way. I can just lose myself in a whole new world whenever I want.

Text.SourceString: It’s escapism, so to speak.//<portrait=happy>Even when life's good, it's kinda cool to explore some underworld or jet off to a galaxy far, far away.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s escapism, so to speak.//<portrait=happy>Even when life's good, it's kinda cool to explore some underworld or jet off to a galaxy far, far away.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I kinda miss my fam. I find myself missing mom a tad bit more than dad, haha!//Don't get me wrong, I love them both, it's just...you know, different bonds.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I kinda miss my fam. I find myself missing mom a tad bit more than dad, haha!//Don't get me wrong, I love them both, it's just...you know, different bonds.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Luke</> hired me to take some pictures of the vineyard one time, and I fell in love with it.//<portrait=happy>It’s just so beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Luke</> hired me to take some pictures of the vineyard one time, and I fell in love with it.//<portrait=happy>It’s just so beautiful.

Text.SourceString: I bet your farm would be great to photograph!//<portrait=happy>Maybe when I have the time, I can stop by and take pictures of you in action.
Text.LocalizedString: I bet your farm would be great to photograph!//<portrait=happy>Maybe when I have the time, I can stop by and take pictures of you in action.

Text.SourceString: The only time you'll catch me taking a selfie is when my folks need "proof" I'm actually going around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: The only time you'll catch me taking a selfie is when my folks need "proof" I'm actually going around the island.

Text.SourceString: My mom's the one who showed me the ropes of photography.
Text.LocalizedString: My mom's the one who showed me the ropes of photography.

Text.SourceString: She's not some big-shot professional...nah... She's just always been our go-to for family photos.//Weddings, birthdays, those goofy zoo trips, baby's first steps, first haircut. If it's a memory, she's got it in a frame.
Text.LocalizedString: She's not some big-shot professional...nah... She's just always been our go-to for family photos.//Weddings, birthdays, those goofy zoo trips, baby's first steps, first haircut. If it's a memory, she's got it in a frame.

Text.SourceString: Pizza? Oh yeah. I love it!//<portrait=normal>It’s delicious. You can have cheese, vegetables… Mmm! Yummy.
Text.LocalizedString: Pizza? Oh yeah. I love it!//<portrait=normal>It’s delicious. You can have cheese, vegetables… Mmm! Yummy.

Text.SourceString: There's something special about capturing the ever-changing face of nature.//It shows us a new face every day.
Text.LocalizedString: There's something special about capturing the ever-changing face of nature.//It shows us a new face every day.

Text.SourceString: My parents surprised me with a TV! Can you even?//<portrait=normal>They know I like video games, and they knew I could use a new one. Sweet, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: My parents surprised me with a TV! Can you even?//<portrait=normal>They know I like video games, and they knew I could use a new one. Sweet, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: You're a regular at the cavern, aren't you? I see you there quite a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: You're a regular at the cavern, aren't you? I see you there quite a bit.

Text.SourceString: Don’t worry! I'm not tailing you or anything. Ha!//<portrait=normal>I tend to hang around the forest a lot too. Epic photo ops!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t worry! I'm not tailing you or anything. Ha!//<portrait=normal>I tend to hang around the forest a lot too. Epic photo ops!

Text.SourceString: The girls at the inn always suggest getting dinner together.//Little things like that make me feel right at home.
Text.LocalizedString: The girls at the inn always suggest getting dinner together.//Little things like that make me feel right at home.

Text.SourceString: They're like my chosen fam.
Text.LocalizedString: They're like my chosen fam.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eva</> has some skills with a needle and thread. She can sew up just about anything!//<portrait=happy>It’s so awesome!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Eva</> has some skills with a needle and thread. She can sew up just about anything!//<portrait=happy>It’s so awesome!

Text.SourceString: I notice different flowers bloom each season.//It’s hard to pick a favorite with that many options.
Text.LocalizedString: I notice different flowers bloom each season.//It’s hard to pick a favorite with that many options.

Text.SourceString: But keep an eye out for flowers like lilies.//They're season hoppers. Summer and Fall bloomers, if I remember right.
Text.LocalizedString: But keep an eye out for flowers like lilies.//They're season hoppers. Summer and Fall bloomers, if I remember right.

Text.SourceString: Listening is like, a superpower. Give people the space to talk about themselves and you'll really get to know them.
Text.LocalizedString: Listening is like, a superpower. Give people the space to talk about themselves and you'll really get to know them.

Text.SourceString: I've uncovered so much about people this way.
Text.LocalizedString: I've uncovered so much about people this way.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to the beach or heading back home?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to the beach or heading back home?

Text.SourceString: Not a whole lot going on here. Just working on stacking my portfolio.//<portrait=normal>Fingers crossed, one of these snapshots might just score me a sweet job.
Text.LocalizedString: Not a whole lot going on here. Just working on stacking my portfolio.//<portrait=normal>Fingers crossed, one of these snapshots might just score me a sweet job.

Text.SourceString: Yeesh, there sure are a lot of mosquitoes here. I swear the heat just amps them up.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeesh, there sure are a lot of mosquitoes here. I swear the heat just amps them up.

Text.SourceString: It also makes me crave fruit tarts. Hmm...//The heat, not the mosquito bit.
Text.LocalizedString: It also makes me crave fruit tarts. Hmm...//The heat, not the mosquito bit.

Text.SourceString: I had the worst night last night. I think <NPCName>Valentina’s</> dad came to visit, and he was so loud in the lobby. I didn’t sleep very well afterward. Kept waking up, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: I had the worst night last night. I think <NPCName>Valentina’s</> dad came to visit, and he was so loud in the lobby. I didn’t sleep very well afterward. Kept waking up, you know?

Text.SourceString: Ah, well. It's all part of the package when you live around people, right?//I mean, sure, I could live in the middle of nowhere like <NPCName>Emma</> and <NPCName>Dippa</>, but I choose not to.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, well. It's all part of the package when you live around people, right?//I mean, sure, I could live in the middle of nowhere like <NPCName>Emma</> and <NPCName>Dippa</>, but I choose not to.

Text.SourceString: This goes without saying, but please don’t tell anyone. I don’t want to make a fuss over nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: This goes without saying, but please don’t tell anyone. I don’t want to make a fuss over nothing.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting along great with the twins at the inn. You know them too, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting along great with the twins at the inn. You know them too, right?

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll make pizza tomorrow for everyone at the inn. Nice little hangout sesh before the week kicks off, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll make pizza tomorrow for everyone at the inn. Nice little hangout sesh before the week kicks off, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: Nothing’s set in stone yet, though. For starters, I don’t even have any cheese.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothing’s set in stone yet, though. For starters, I don’t even have any cheese.

Text.SourceString: Spring colors are gorgeous here.//It’s my time to farm photos!
Text.LocalizedString: Spring colors are gorgeous here.//It’s my time to farm photos!

Text.SourceString: I think my favorite place to take photos in Spring is around the lake.//<portrait=blushing>The old temple looks just beautiful surrounded by cherry blossoms.
Text.LocalizedString: I think my favorite place to take photos in Spring is around the lake.//<portrait=blushing>The old temple looks just beautiful surrounded by cherry blossoms.

Text.SourceString: Oh wow, it’s Spring already!//I’m excited to take Stephen out again and show him around.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh wow, it’s Spring already!//I’m excited to take Stephen out again and show him around.

Text.SourceString: I like to take photos of the leaves as they grow. It’s beautiful and poetic, you know?//Yeah! It <Italic>does</> show progression.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to take photos of the leaves as they grow. It’s beautiful and poetic, you know?//Yeah! It <Italic>does</> show progression.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Mr. Mayor</> hires me to document the festivals. He pays pretty well.//Let’s see, up next is the Cherry Blossom Festival on the 10th.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Mr. Mayor</> hires me to document the festivals. He pays pretty well.//Let’s see, up next is the Cherry Blossom Festival on the 10th.

Text.SourceString: There’s a new Resident Vile game coming out this Summer.//Not sure if I'll get it, though. My schedule's pretty packed. I think I’ll just watch someone stream it or something.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a new Resident Vile game coming out this Summer.//Not sure if I'll get it, though. My schedule's pretty packed. I think I’ll just watch someone stream it or something.

Text.SourceString: Besides, I don’t think it’ll be on consoles yet.//My laptop isn’t powerful enough to run it smoothly. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, I don’t think it’ll be on consoles yet.//My laptop isn’t powerful enough to run it smoothly. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Summer snapshots of Coral Island are just the bomb! I mean, come on, who wouldn't wanna see a beautiful island in full Summer bloom, right?//<portrait=blushing>It’s all about those vibrant Summer vibes!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer snapshots of Coral Island are just the bomb! I mean, come on, who wouldn't wanna see a beautiful island in full Summer bloom, right?//<portrait=blushing>It’s all about those vibrant Summer vibes!

Text.SourceString: I feel super blessed to live so close to the beach. I can bring my lil' buddy Stephen out for a beach run any time I feel like it.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel super blessed to live so close to the beach. I can bring my lil' buddy Stephen out for a beach run any time I feel like it.

Text.SourceString: Plus, the sunrise and sunset photo ops are just endless! Not that I’m out there every day, but hey, I totally could be!
Text.LocalizedString: Plus, the sunrise and sunset photo ops are just endless! Not that I’m out there every day, but hey, I totally could be!

Text.SourceString: Stephen is my little ray of sunshine. He just can't get enough of the beach.//He's practically bouncing with joy inside his tank, every time we go for a walk there.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen is my little ray of sunshine. He just can't get enough of the beach.//He's practically bouncing with joy inside his tank, every time we go for a walk there.

Text.SourceString: I like wearing boots. I know the weather is a bit hot, but they give me great support for walking.//So I don’t accidentally stumble on a rock and fall while I’m holding the camera.
Text.LocalizedString: I like wearing boots. I know the weather is a bit hot, but they give me great support for walking.//So I don’t accidentally stumble on a rock and fall while I’m holding the camera.

Text.SourceString: I wish it wasn’t so humid.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish it wasn’t so humid.

Text.SourceString: I know you can make fruit tarts whenever, but it always feels like a Summer dish to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I know you can make fruit tarts whenever, but it always feels like a Summer dish to me.

Text.SourceString: I <Italic>love</> taking beach photos in Summer. Maybe it's basic, but who cares?
Text.LocalizedString: I <Italic>love</> taking beach photos in Summer. Maybe it's basic, but who cares?

Text.SourceString: Wowza, it’s Summer already! Time for the community beach cleanup. I’m mulling over whether to take Stephen along.//He’d be good company.
Text.LocalizedString: Wowza, it’s Summer already! Time for the community beach cleanup. I’m mulling over whether to take Stephen along.//He’d be good company.

Text.SourceString: Would it be okay if I take photos of you during the Beach Cleanup Festival?//I take photos of the event. Just wanna make sure I have your consent.
Text.LocalizedString: Would it be okay if I take photos of you during the Beach Cleanup Festival?//I take photos of the event. Just wanna make sure I have your consent.

Text.SourceString: Pizza is food for all seasons.//Chilly Winter night? Awesome! Scorching Summer day like today? Even better!
Text.LocalizedString: Pizza is food for all seasons.//Chilly Winter night? Awesome! Scorching Summer day like today? Even better!

Text.SourceString: I think Fall is just... Oh my gosh, <Italic>just</> so pretty! No matter where you are.//But here on Coral Island? It’s like Fall on steroids!
Text.LocalizedString: I think Fall is just... Oh my gosh, <Italic>just</> so pretty! No matter where you are.//But here on Coral Island? It’s like Fall on steroids!

Text.SourceString: Taking photos in Fall can be a bit tricky. The composition has to be just right or it's just...blah. But when it works, it's magic!
Text.LocalizedString: Taking photos in Fall can be a bit tricky. The composition has to be just right or it's just...blah. But when it works, it's magic!

Text.SourceString: I don’t really have a fave season. Coral Island is stunning all year round, which is why I just had to move here.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really have a fave season. Coral Island is stunning all year round, which is why I just had to move here.

Text.SourceString: The Harvest Festival is just packed with fun! And the photo ops? Don’t even get me started!
Text.LocalizedString: The Harvest Festival is just packed with fun! And the photo ops? Don’t even get me started!

Text.SourceString: I like taking photos of Stephen in Fall. His blue shell stands out beautifully in the Fall colors.
Text.LocalizedString: I like taking photos of Stephen in Fall. His blue shell stands out beautifully in the Fall colors.

Text.SourceString: Wowza, it’s Fall already! The island is going to look so pretty with the orange leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: Wowza, it’s Fall already! The island is going to look so pretty with the orange leaves.

Text.SourceString: I can’t take Stephen for walks in Winter. It’s kind of sad, but he doesn’t like the cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t take Stephen for walks in Winter. It’s kind of sad, but he doesn’t like the cold.

Text.SourceString: I have Stephen’s tank heated during Winter. He’s a lot more lively when the water is warmer.//I wanna get one of those smart thermometers for fish tanks, but they cost too much. So the manual one will do for now.
Text.LocalizedString: I have Stephen’s tank heated during Winter. He’s a lot more lively when the water is warmer.//I wanna get one of those smart thermometers for fish tanks, but they cost too much. So the manual one will do for now.

Text.SourceString: Coral Island is always beautiful, no matter the season.//<portrait=blushing>When Winter wraps everything in a snow blanket, it's like stepping into a peaceful, enchanting dreamland.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island is always beautiful, no matter the season.//<portrait=blushing>When Winter wraps everything in a snow blanket, it's like stepping into a peaceful, enchanting dreamland.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I worry something’s wrong with Stephen, but then I remember it’s Winter, and he’s just going to be less active than usual.//Do you think I should have <NPCName>Yuri</> check him out? Can she even?
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I worry something’s wrong with Stephen, but then I remember it’s Winter, and he’s just going to be less active than usual.//Do you think I should have <NPCName>Yuri</> check him out? Can she even?

Text.SourceString: Sure, it's chilly, but I'm a shorts girl through and through.//I move easier in them. Less restricting.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, it's chilly, but I'm a shorts girl through and through.//I move easier in them. Less restricting.

Text.SourceString: Oh wow, it’s Winter already! No wonder Stephen looks a bit lethargic.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh wow, it’s Winter already! No wonder Stephen looks a bit lethargic.

Text.SourceString: Every time I take a photo of the island in Winter, I think “Winter wonderland.” It really is a wonder!
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I take a photo of the island in Winter, I think “Winter wonderland.” It really is a wonder!

Text.SourceString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. It's one of the job perks.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. It's one of the job perks.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.

Text.SourceString: I’m starting to feel the heat... And mosquito bites.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m starting to feel the heat... And mosquito bites.

Text.SourceString: If you pay close attention to your surroundings, you can spot wild animals on the island.
Text.LocalizedString: If you pay close attention to your surroundings, you can spot wild animals on the island.

Text.SourceString: Birds’ nests are always nice to spot. This one time, I took progress pictures of eggs in a nest until they hatched.
Text.LocalizedString: Birds’ nests are always nice to spot. This one time, I took progress pictures of eggs in a nest until they hatched.

Text.SourceString: It took quite a while, but it was worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: It took quite a while, but it was worth it.

Text.SourceString: Harvest season is coming up, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re about to get really busy, aren’t you?
Text.LocalizedString: Harvest season is coming up, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re about to get really busy, aren’t you?

Text.SourceString: I’m going to take it easy today. I’m still so tired from the beach cleanup.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to take it easy today. I’m still so tired from the beach cleanup.

Text.SourceString: We don’t have anything going on until the third week of Fall.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t have anything going on until the third week of Fall.

Text.SourceString: Um, the Harvest Festival on the 15th is the next one.
Text.LocalizedString: Um, the Harvest Festival on the 15th is the next one.

Text.SourceString: Can you believe it’s the 11th already? Winter is literally right around the corner.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you believe it’s the 11th already? Winter is literally right around the corner.

Text.SourceString: Yikes. I need to find my coat. It snows pretty hard here.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes. I need to find my coat. It snows pretty hard here.

Text.SourceString: If my mom found out I was wearing shorts on a windy day like this, I’d be in deep trouble. Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: If my mom found out I was wearing shorts on a windy day like this, I’d be in deep trouble. Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: Anything cool going on today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Anything cool going on today, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Get it? ’Cause it’s Winter… Cool…//<portrait=blushing>Heh heh!
Text.LocalizedString: Get it? ’Cause it’s Winter… Cool…//<portrait=blushing>Heh heh!

Text.SourceString: A lot of cool things happen here in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: A lot of cool things happen here in Winter.

Text.SourceString: The Winter Fair is one of them, happening on the 21st.//<portrait=surprised>Wait, it's the 20th, my bad. The anticipation is getting to me!
Text.LocalizedString: The Winter Fair is one of them, happening on the 21st.//<portrait=surprised>Wait, it's the 20th, my bad. The anticipation is getting to me!

Text.SourceString: Are you planting anything this Winter?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planting anything this Winter?

Text.SourceString: Whoa, it’s a busy year for you. Must be tiring to be farming all year round.
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, it’s a busy year for you. Must be tiring to be farming all year round.

Special.SourceString: Yeah, farming like usual, except in the cold.
Special.LocalizedString: Yeah, farming like usual, except in the cold.

Text.SourceString: That’s great, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s good to take a break once in a while and just enjoy this island. After all, isn’t that why we’re all here?
Text.LocalizedString: That’s great, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s good to take a break once in a while and just enjoy this island. After all, isn’t that why we’re all here?

Special.SourceString: Nah, I’ll farm again in the spring.
Special.LocalizedString: Nah, I’ll farm again in the spring.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eva</> and I wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow, but they said no because the New Year’s Eve party’s in two days.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Eva</> and I wanted to throw a simple party for the twins’ birthday tomorrow, but they said no because the New Year’s Eve party’s in two days.

Text.SourceString: Oh well. Their call, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well. Their call, right?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Erika</> is good at cutting curly hair. She takes care of mine.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Erika</> is good at cutting curly hair. She takes care of mine.

Text.SourceString: I'll let the rain mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll let the rain mellow out a bit, then unleash my camera.

Text.SourceString: It looks quite muddy out there. I don’t wanna slip and fall.
Text.LocalizedString: It looks quite muddy out there. I don’t wanna slip and fall.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, what should I have for dinner?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, what should I have for dinner?

Text.SourceString: Stephen gets his meals twice a day. I wanna make sure he gets all the nutrients he needs, but I don’t want to overfeed him.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen gets his meals twice a day. I wanna make sure he gets all the nutrients he needs, but I don’t want to overfeed him.

Text.SourceString: Can you hold on one sec? I’m in a boss battle.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you hold on one sec? I’m in a boss battle.

Text.SourceString: Yikes. It’s storming really hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes. It’s storming really hard.

Text.SourceString: The wind is a bit scary, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is a bit scary, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: This storm is giving me a bit of anxiety. It’s been windy all day, and the deck isn’t exactly brand new.
Text.LocalizedString: This storm is giving me a bit of anxiety. It’s been windy all day, and the deck isn’t exactly brand new.

Text.SourceString: *nervous chuckle*
Text.LocalizedString: *nervous chuckle*

Text.SourceString: I settled for a yearly deal at the inn. They offer me a sweet rate, and in return, I snap some pics for them. No charge.
Text.LocalizedString: I settled for a yearly deal at the inn. They offer me a sweet rate, and in return, I snap some pics for them. No charge.

Text.SourceString: The photos cost me close to nothing, so living here is dirt cheap at the end of the day.
Text.LocalizedString: The photos cost me close to nothing, so living here is dirt cheap at the end of the day.

Text.SourceString: The sand can be scorching on bare feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The sand can be scorching on bare feet.

Text.SourceString: This beach is where I found Stephen. Right over there, in fact!//Poor guy lost a claw, so I've given him a safe place to sprout a new one.
Text.LocalizedString: This beach is where I found Stephen. Right over there, in fact!//Poor guy lost a claw, so I've given him a safe place to sprout a new one.

Text.SourceString: I search the beach every so often for injured animals. Thankfully, I haven’t found any besides Stephen so far.
Text.LocalizedString: I search the beach every so often for injured animals. Thankfully, I haven’t found any besides Stephen so far.

Text.SourceString: Fun fact, Stephen's a male lobster. I’m pretty sure.
Text.LocalizedString: Fun fact, Stephen's a male lobster. I’m pretty sure.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Kenny</> and I did a little check. Stephen's got pointy first pair of swimmerets, so he's a male.//Female lobsters sport thin, feathery ones.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Kenny</> and I did a little check. Stephen's got pointy first pair of swimmerets, so he's a male.//Female lobsters sport thin, feathery ones.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Macy</> is having fun.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Macy</> is having fun.]

Text.SourceString: This is my go-to spot when I feel like treating myself to a home-cooked meal and cold drinks.
Text.LocalizedString: This is my go-to spot when I feel like treating myself to a home-cooked meal and cold drinks.

Text.SourceString: I was told <NPCName>Frank</> cooks everything on the menu himself.
Text.LocalizedString: I was told <NPCName>Frank</> cooks everything on the menu himself.

Text.SourceString: Why would you wanna cook if you can get someone to do it for you, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Why would you wanna cook if you can get someone to do it for you, right?

Text.SourceString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.

Text.SourceString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.

Text.SourceString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s much warmer here than at the inn.

Text.SourceString: There are plenty of nature and photography books here for inspiration.
Text.LocalizedString: There are plenty of nature and photography books here for inspiration.

Text.SourceString: There’s information about farming and fishing too, isn’t there?
Text.LocalizedString: There’s information about farming and fishing too, isn’t there?

Text.SourceString: You can nap here, and as long as you don’t snore, I think you can get away with it.
Text.LocalizedString: You can nap here, and as long as you don’t snore, I think you can get away with it.

Text.SourceString: Stephen sure loves his tank. I splurged my entire monthly grocery allowance building it. Survived the month on foraging and instant noodles.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen sure loves his tank. I splurged my entire monthly grocery allowance building it. Survived the month on foraging and instant noodles.

Text.SourceString: Brought back the good ol' uni days.
Text.LocalizedString: Brought back the good ol' uni days.

Text.SourceString: I thought about becoming a farmer too, but I couldn’t see myself committing to staying in one spot for such a long time.
Text.LocalizedString: I thought about becoming a farmer too, but I couldn’t see myself committing to staying in one spot for such a long time.

Text.SourceString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. I think it’s one of the advantages of this line of work.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t get too stressed, thankfully. I think it’s one of the advantages of this line of work.//I’m always surrounded by nature and pretty things. It puts me in a good mood, always.

Text.SourceString: Do you feel a gust of wind? It’s making me sleepy.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you feel a gust of wind? It’s making me sleepy.

Text.SourceString: Where’s the wind coming from anyway? Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Where’s the wind coming from anyway? Hmm…

Text.SourceString: Reaching this place feels like a mini workout.
Text.LocalizedString: Reaching this place feels like a mini workout.

Text.SourceString: I had a big bowl of avocado for breakfast this morning.//<portrait=happy>What did you have?
Text.LocalizedString: I had a big bowl of avocado for breakfast this morning.//<portrait=happy>What did you have?

Text.SourceString: I used to work for a corporation, dealing with financial records, before I decided to try my luck at photography.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to work for a corporation, dealing with financial records, before I decided to try my luck at photography.

Text.SourceString: I love it so far. I get to meet people with interesting stories and take pretty pictures of nature.
Text.LocalizedString: I love it so far. I get to meet people with interesting stories and take pretty pictures of nature.

Text.SourceString: Other interests? Uh. Um. I like video games! And I like people. And I like my rescue lobster, Stephen!
Text.LocalizedString: Other interests? Uh. Um. I like video games! And I like people. And I like my rescue lobster, Stephen!

Text.SourceString: Guess that doesn't sound like a ton, does it? Eh.
Text.LocalizedString: Guess that doesn't sound like a ton, does it? Eh.

Text.SourceString: Degrees and certificates aren’t everything. They help when you’re starting out, but I never took more than a few photography classes.
Text.LocalizedString: Degrees and certificates aren’t everything. They help when you’re starting out, but I never took more than a few photography classes.

Text.SourceString: I actually have a degree in finance! Funny, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I actually have a degree in finance! Funny, right?

Text.SourceString: This island is so beautiful. It’s hard to take a bad photo!
Text.LocalizedString: This island is so beautiful. It’s hard to take a bad photo!

Text.SourceString: Not that every picture I take here is a winner. Composition matters too. But still!
Text.LocalizedString: Not that every picture I take here is a winner. Composition matters too. But still!

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>,<PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Just trying to lock your name in my memory! Read somewhere it's easier when you repeat someone's name while looking at them.
Text.LocalizedString: Just trying to lock your name in my memory! Read somewhere it's easier when you repeat someone's name while looking at them.

Text.SourceString: Do you have any photography experience, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have any photography experience, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Hey, that’s fine!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, that’s fine!

Special.SourceString: Just selfies and such, nothing impressive.
Special.LocalizedString: Just selfies and such, nothing impressive.

Text.SourceString: Amazing! I, like, never get to geek out about framing and cool lenses and stuff except on the internet.
Text.LocalizedString: Amazing! I, like, never get to geek out about framing and cool lenses and stuff except on the internet.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha! Don’t worry, I do too. But that doesn’t mean you can’t learn to love taking them!
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha! Don’t worry, I do too. But that doesn’t mean you can’t learn to love taking them!

Special.SourceString: I hate even being in pictures, so…
Special.LocalizedString: I hate even being in pictures, so…

Text.SourceString: Hold on. I just spotted an <Italic>amazing</> shot!
Text.LocalizedString: Hold on. I just spotted an <Italic>amazing</> shot!

Text.SourceString: Blah. I need more caffeine.
Text.LocalizedString: Blah. I need more caffeine.

Text.SourceString: Our world is truly a masterpiece. Protecting that beauty is the best gig in the universe.
Text.LocalizedString: Our world is truly a masterpiece. Protecting that beauty is the best gig in the universe.

Text.SourceString: My weekly walks with Stephen are important. He really seems to enjoy them.
Text.LocalizedString: My weekly walks with Stephen are important. He really seems to enjoy them.

Text.SourceString: What's up?
Text.LocalizedString: What's up?

Text.SourceString: Coral Island has some neat local legends. I wonder which of ’em are true.
Text.LocalizedString: Coral Island has some neat local legends. I wonder which of ’em are true.

Text.SourceString: I need a lot of space. My freedom is important to me.
Text.LocalizedString: I need a lot of space. My freedom is important to me.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever miss your family back home? It’s nice to be free, but I still miss my parents.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever miss your family back home? It’s nice to be free, but I still miss my parents.

Text.SourceString: You’re…in my way. Move, please.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re…in my way. Move, please.

Text.SourceString: Oh, Stephen is my only pet. Any more, and my worry meter would explode!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, Stephen is my only pet. Any more, and my worry meter would explode!

Text.SourceString: How goes the farming? Is it <Italic>farmy</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How goes the farming? Is it <Italic>farmy</>?

Text.SourceString: You into video games? These days it's hard to find someone who doesn't at least dabble in mobile gaming.
Text.LocalizedString: You into video games? These days it's hard to find someone who doesn't at least dabble in mobile gaming.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a hardcore gamer or anything, but indie games hold a special place in my heart!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a hardcore gamer or anything, but indie games hold a special place in my heart!

Text.SourceString: Being a photographer means I have to be ready to whip out my camera at a moment’s notice.
Text.LocalizedString: Being a photographer means I have to be ready to whip out my camera at a moment’s notice.

Text.SourceString: There’ve been dozens, if not hundreds, of shots that got away. They haunt me, <PlayerName>$player</>. They haunt me.
Text.LocalizedString: There’ve been dozens, if not hundreds, of shots that got away. They haunt me, <PlayerName>$player</>. They haunt me.

Text.SourceString: Living on such a small island is weird. You eventually know everything about everyone.
Text.LocalizedString: Living on such a small island is weird. You eventually know everything about everyone.

Text.SourceString: I guess you can also say it’s nice. Intimate, maybe?
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you can also say it’s nice. Intimate, maybe?

Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t say I have any particularly close friends. But I’m not a loner, either.
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t say I have any particularly close friends. But I’m not a loner, either.

Text.SourceString: You know what’s funny? I don’t like raw fruit, but I love, love, love baked fruit.
Text.LocalizedString: You know what’s funny? I don’t like raw fruit, but I love, love, love baked fruit.

Text.SourceString: It’s a sensory thing! I just hate the texture of uncooked fruit, but once you bake it? Hoo!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a sensory thing! I just hate the texture of uncooked fruit, but once you bake it? Hoo!

Text.SourceString: Can you cook? Well, you’re a farmer. I’m sure you can. I can’t, though!
Text.LocalizedString: Can you cook? Well, you’re a farmer. I’m sure you can. I can’t, though!

Text.SourceString: I’ve worked hard to give Stephen a good life. Once he regrows his claw, though, I’ll return him to the wild.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve worked hard to give Stephen a good life. Once he regrows his claw, though, I’ll return him to the wild.

Text.SourceString: Mmm… I could really go for a snack right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Mmm… I could really go for a snack right now.

Text.SourceString: Pretty much everyone in town has given me permission to take pictures of them.
Text.LocalizedString: Pretty much everyone in town has given me permission to take pictures of them.

Text.SourceString: There are a few exceptions! All for good reasons.
Text.LocalizedString: There are a few exceptions! All for good reasons.

Text.SourceString: Most of my work so far has been nature photography, so I’m really good at framing that specific type of shot.
Text.LocalizedString: Most of my work so far has been nature photography, so I’m really good at framing that specific type of shot.

Text.SourceString: I’m wondering if I should expand my work to other things, though.//<portrait=annoyed>What if it gets boring? Buh!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m wondering if I should expand my work to other things, though.//<portrait=annoyed>What if it gets boring? Buh!

Text.SourceString: If it’s one goose, two geese, why not one moose, two meese? I’m so confused.
Text.LocalizedString: If it’s one goose, two geese, why not one moose, two meese? I’m so confused.

Text.SourceString: Do you like to dance, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I do!//It’s great to let your energy out sometimes, even if you look goofy.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you like to dance, <PlayerName>$player</>? I know I do!//It’s great to let your energy out sometimes, even if you look goofy.

Text.SourceString: My best pictures all play with composition in unexpected ways.//One of my favorites is of a bird of paradise, looking all regal.
Text.LocalizedString: My best pictures all play with composition in unexpected ways.//One of my favorites is of a bird of paradise, looking all regal.

Text.SourceString: But if you look in the corner, you can see a cat with huge eyes, creeping up on him!
Text.LocalizedString: But if you look in the corner, you can see a cat with huge eyes, creeping up on him!

Text.SourceString: I got the shot just in time. I lowered my camera, and the bird shrieked and took flight!//<portrait=normal>It was hysterical.
Text.LocalizedString: I got the shot just in time. I lowered my camera, and the bird shrieked and took flight!//<portrait=normal>It was hysterical.

Text.SourceString: I hope Stephen’s okay. Well, I’m sure he is, but I still worry.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope Stephen’s okay. Well, I’m sure he is, but I still worry.

Text.SourceString: It can take some time before you figure out what you want to do in life. It did for both of us, right?
Text.LocalizedString: It can take some time before you figure out what you want to do in life. It did for both of us, right?

Text.SourceString: I was working a corporate job like you for a while before I became a photographer.
Text.LocalizedString: I was working a corporate job like you for a while before I became a photographer.

Text.SourceString: I had the weirdest dream last night. I was a pickle, and everyone was standing around me, laughing.
Text.LocalizedString: I had the weirdest dream last night. I was a pickle, and everyone was standing around me, laughing.

Text.SourceString: People always expect you to be constantly friendly and upbeat.//It’s exhausting.
Text.LocalizedString: People always expect you to be constantly friendly and upbeat.//It’s exhausting.

Text.SourceString: I try to be friendly, but I want it to be on my terms!
Text.LocalizedString: I try to be friendly, but I want it to be on my terms!

Text.SourceString: Chocolate sounds great right now.//<portrait=happy>I’d love some hot chocolate.
Text.LocalizedString: Chocolate sounds great right now.//<portrait=happy>I’d love some hot chocolate.

Text.SourceString: I had a video call with my parents today. They were happy to see me, and I was happy to see them.
Text.LocalizedString: I had a video call with my parents today. They were happy to see me, and I was happy to see them.

Text.SourceString: Drinking coffee takes too long. Maybe I should just snort instant espresso powder.
Text.LocalizedString: Drinking coffee takes too long. Maybe I should just snort instant espresso powder.

Text.SourceString: I’m kidding! I’m kidding!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m kidding! I’m kidding!

Text.SourceString: Half the time when I make a joke, people assume I’m serious. I wonder why.
Text.LocalizedString: Half the time when I make a joke, people assume I’m serious. I wonder why.

Text.SourceString: I like coming here just to think about things. The ocean clears my head.
Text.LocalizedString: I like coming here just to think about things. The ocean clears my head.

Text.SourceString: Don’tcha just love that sea-salt scent? Ha! That’s fun to say. Sea-salt scent!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’tcha just love that sea-salt scent? Ha! That’s fun to say. Sea-salt scent!

Text.SourceString: I love the dim lights here. I can handle loud noises just fine. It’s my eyes that are too sensitive.
Text.LocalizedString: I love the dim lights here. I can handle loud noises just fine. It’s my eyes that are too sensitive.

Text.SourceString: There are some awesome photography books here. <NPCName>Millie</> got some just for me! She’s a real doll.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some awesome photography books here. <NPCName>Millie</> got some just for me! She’s a real doll.

Text.SourceString: Hmm, which orientation should I choose? Landscape or portrait?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm, which orientation should I choose? Landscape or portrait?

Text.SourceString: Hang on, I need to change my lens.
Text.LocalizedString: Hang on, I need to change my lens.

Text.SourceString: The light on the sea is perfect. <PlayerName>$player</>, look at that!
Text.LocalizedString: The light on the sea is perfect. <PlayerName>$player</>, look at that!

Text.SourceString: Buh! The sun is so bright today, it hurts my eyes. But it’s such good lighting for photography.
Text.LocalizedString: Buh! The sun is so bright today, it hurts my eyes. But it’s such good lighting for photography.

Text.SourceString: My head hurts. It’s the light. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: My head hurts. It’s the light. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.

Text.SourceString: It’s so cold out there! I’d bundle up a little more if I were you.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so cold out there! I’d bundle up a little more if I were you.

Text.SourceString: So much snow! Wish I had taller boots. My socks are getting soaked.
Text.LocalizedString: So much snow! Wish I had taller boots. My socks are getting soaked.

Text.SourceString: When it storms, it literally goes all day. How do the clouds not run out of water?
Text.LocalizedString: When it storms, it literally goes all day. How do the clouds not run out of water?

Text.SourceString: I bet I could get some awesome lightning shots if I were patient enough! But I’m tired.
Text.LocalizedString: I bet I could get some awesome lightning shots if I were patient enough! But I’m tired.

Text.SourceString: I was nervous when I told my parents I wanted to pursue photography for a living.//But one thing I learned from them was never to live someone else’s life.
Text.LocalizedString: I was nervous when I told my parents I wanted to pursue photography for a living.//But one thing I learned from them was never to live someone else’s life.

Text.SourceString: I guess I had no reason to be nervous, because my parents were always supportive of me.//<portrait=annoyed>Sometimes you can’t help feeling that way, though. Even when I’m relaxing, playing games, hanging out at the coffee shop, worries just come with no warning. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I had no reason to be nervous, because my parents were always supportive of me.//<portrait=annoyed>Sometimes you can’t help feeling that way, though. Even when I’m relaxing, playing games, hanging out at the coffee shop, worries just come with no warning. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: You know, <PlayerName>$player</>, having you around makes me feel less lonely.//<portrait=normal>I do miss my parents sometimes, but I miss them less when I’m with you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, <PlayerName>$player</>, having you around makes me feel less lonely.//<portrait=normal>I do miss my parents sometimes, but I miss them less when I’m with you.

Text.SourceString: I kind of like it.
Text.LocalizedString: I kind of like it.

Text.SourceString: You remind me of my friend Jo.//<portrait=concerned>We were pretty close, but then we lost touch. Just like that.//I’m gonna reach out sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: You remind me of my friend Jo.//<portrait=concerned>We were pretty close, but then we lost touch. Just like that.//I’m gonna reach out sometime.

Text.SourceString: We didn’t fall out or anything. Life happened.
Text.LocalizedString: We didn’t fall out or anything. Life happened.

Text.SourceString: Stephen is the closest thing to a sibling that I have. As an only child, I never had to share a room or anything.
Text.LocalizedString: Stephen is the closest thing to a sibling that I have. As an only child, I never had to share a room or anything.

Text.SourceString: That sounded really sad when I said it out loud like that. Ha ha!//<portrait=normal>It actually wasn’t sad at all, so please don’t take it the wrong way.
Text.LocalizedString: That sounded really sad when I said it out loud like that. Ha ha!//<portrait=normal>It actually wasn’t sad at all, so please don’t take it the wrong way.

Text.SourceString: What’s the deal with pickles? Why are they so sour and crunchy?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s the deal with pickles? Why are they so sour and crunchy?

Text.SourceString: Pickles kind of ruin food for me. Not a fan.
Text.LocalizedString: Pickles kind of ruin food for me. Not a fan.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I was just thinking about visiting you at the farm.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I was just thinking about visiting you at the farm.

Text.SourceString: I wanted to show you a photo of Stephen that I took last night. He was wearing a tiny pumpkin hat.//He was being so cute!//<portrait=annoyed>Ah darn! I don’t have it with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanted to show you a photo of Stephen that I took last night. He was wearing a tiny pumpkin hat.//He was being so cute!//<portrait=annoyed>Ah darn! I don’t have it with me.

Text.SourceString: Tell me this. Does it really matter if we go through life without ever finding our true passion?
Text.LocalizedString: Tell me this. Does it really matter if we go through life without ever finding our true passion?

Text.SourceString: My cousin, who lives in Pokyo, works from Monday to Thursday, then she hangs out with her friends on the weekend.//Plays games a little and takes a vacation once or twice a year. She told me she doesn’t feel passionate about anything, but she’s happy.
Text.LocalizedString: My cousin, who lives in Pokyo, works from Monday to Thursday, then she hangs out with her friends on the weekend.//Plays games a little and takes a vacation once or twice a year. She told me she doesn’t feel passionate about anything, but she’s happy.

Text.SourceString: Not everyone will find their passion. Some people go through life just trying to keep up with their responsibilities.//And that’s okay, I think. As long as we’re happy.
Text.LocalizedString: Not everyone will find their passion. Some people go through life just trying to keep up with their responsibilities.//And that’s okay, I think. As long as we’re happy.

Text.SourceString: The inn gets very lonely sometimes. Hmm. You must get lonely up there too, I imagine.
Text.LocalizedString: The inn gets very lonely sometimes. Hmm. You must get lonely up there too, I imagine.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking about us last night.//<portrait=blushing>You know. Maybe it wouldn’t be a bad idea for us to play games together sometime. Or have a picnic.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking about us last night.//<portrait=blushing>You know. Maybe it wouldn’t be a bad idea for us to play games together sometime. Or have a picnic.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Walter</> is certainly knowledgeable. The last time I spoke to him, he went on about how I should make a will and start getting my assets valued. I don’t know.//<portrait=concerned>I feel kinda too young and too <Italic>broke</> to think about stuff like that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Walter</> is certainly knowledgeable. The last time I spoke to him, he went on about how I should make a will and start getting my assets valued. I don’t know.//<portrait=concerned>I feel kinda too young and too <Italic>broke</> to think about stuff like that.

Text.SourceString: I was pretty much reluctant, and I think he could tell.//<portrait=normal>Because soon after that, he told me about how making a will has nothing to do with age. Oh well.
Text.LocalizedString: I was pretty much reluctant, and I think he could tell.//<portrait=normal>Because soon after that, he told me about how making a will has nothing to do with age. Oh well.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Oh, it’s so nice to see you.//<portrait=normal>I’ve been <Italic>dying</> to talk to you! How’s the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! Oh, it’s so nice to see you.//<portrait=normal>I’ve been <Italic>dying</> to talk to you! How’s the farm?

Text.SourceString: No, don’t go so soon.//I love listening to you talk about crops and cows and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: No, don’t go so soon.//I love listening to you talk about crops and cows and stuff.

Text.SourceString: Can I tell you something?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I tell you something?

Text.SourceString: I accidentally captured a photo of a masked figure in the forest one time, but I kept it to myself.//<portrait=normal>Some things are better kept secret around here.
Text.LocalizedString: I accidentally captured a photo of a masked figure in the forest one time, but I kept it to myself.//<portrait=normal>Some things are better kept secret around here.

Text.SourceString: Am I too old to have a favorite dinosaur?
Text.LocalizedString: Am I too old to have a favorite dinosaur?

Text.SourceString: Maybe I am, but hey, who cares? I like triceratops.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I am, but hey, who cares? I like triceratops.

Text.SourceString: I went out exploring the other day and found so much fruit on the ground.//I don’t like it, but I didn’t want it to go to waste, so I brought it home.
Text.LocalizedString: I went out exploring the other day and found so much fruit on the ground.//I don’t like it, but I didn’t want it to go to waste, so I brought it home.

Text.SourceString: I suppose my inn mates can eat it if I just put it in the fridge.//<portrait=surprised><Italic>Inn mates</>! Don’t tell them I said that! Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose my inn mates can eat it if I just put it in the fridge.//<portrait=surprised><Italic>Inn mates</>! Don’t tell them I said that! Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: It’s been a while since I’ve been home to see my parents.//I miss them, sure. But to be honest, it’s kind of nice to have a bit of distance.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been a while since I’ve been home to see my parents.//I miss them, sure. But to be honest, it’s kind of nice to have a bit of distance.

Text.SourceString: Yikes. I feel bad saying that out loud.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes. I feel bad saying that out loud.

Text.SourceString: Have you played Battle Oreon? The graphics are out of this world.//You should see it!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you played Battle Oreon? The graphics are out of this world.//You should see it!

Text.SourceString: We should play.//I’ll heat up some pizza and crack open a bottle of wine. It’ll be so much fun.
Text.LocalizedString: We should play.//I’ll heat up some pizza and crack open a bottle of wine. It’ll be so much fun.

Text.SourceString: I love my parents dearly, but I feel like I can’t be myself around them.//Deep down, I’m scared of disappointing them.
Text.LocalizedString: I love my parents dearly, but I feel like I can’t be myself around them.//Deep down, I’m scared of disappointing them.

Text.SourceString: I know my feelings are valid, but I forget sometimes. Thank you for reminding me.//<portrait=concerned>I also feel bad about complaining, because there’s nothing wrong with my life. The guilt eats me up.//You’re a great friend, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I know my feelings are valid, but I forget sometimes. Thank you for reminding me.//<portrait=concerned>I also feel bad about complaining, because there’s nothing wrong with my life. The guilt eats me up.//You’re a great friend, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Being sick makes you miss home. It’s the worst! I hate it.
Text.LocalizedString: Being sick makes you miss home. It’s the worst! I hate it.

Text.SourceString: When I get sick, the girls always keep me company, which is nice. I feel like we have each other’s back at the inn.
Text.LocalizedString: When I get sick, the girls always keep me company, which is nice. I feel like we have each other’s back at the inn.

Text.SourceString: I have other cameras, but this is my favorite. If you want to borrow it, just let me know.
Text.LocalizedString: I have other cameras, but this is my favorite. If you want to borrow it, just let me know.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think living at the inn is a long-term solution.//But it’ll do for now. I don’t want anything permanent just yet.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think living at the inn is a long-term solution.//But it’ll do for now. I don’t want anything permanent just yet.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to have you around. I’d really miss you if you decided to move again.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to have you around. I’d really miss you if you decided to move again.

Text.SourceString: Please don’t.
Text.LocalizedString: Please don’t.

Text.SourceString: Would I be open to staying here for good in the future? It would be hard with my parents so far away.
Text.LocalizedString: Would I be open to staying here for good in the future? It would be hard with my parents so far away.

Text.SourceString: But yeah, if I had a good reason to stay permanently, then I’d do it.//<portrait=normal>Life is short, right? Might as well live it to the fullest.
Text.LocalizedString: But yeah, if I had a good reason to stay permanently, then I’d do it.//<portrait=normal>Life is short, right? Might as well live it to the fullest.

Text.SourceString: I got some <Italic>a-mazing</> shots today! Winter snow, the town. <Italic>Wow!</>//<portrait=normal>Come by my place sometime and check them out, won’t ya?
Text.LocalizedString: I got some <Italic>a-mazing</> shots today! Winter snow, the town. <Italic>Wow!</>//<portrait=normal>Come by my place sometime and check them out, won’t ya?

Text.SourceString: I got some <Italic>a-mazing</> shots today! Diamond beach, the sun. So summery!//<portrait=normal>Come by my place sometime and check them out, won’t ya?
Text.LocalizedString: I got some <Italic>a-mazing</> shots today! Diamond beach, the sun. So summery!//<portrait=normal>Come by my place sometime and check them out, won’t ya?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been playing this game called Inbound lately. You should give it a try sometime!//Its underwater levels are my favorite.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been playing this game called Inbound lately. You should give it a try sometime!//Its underwater levels are my favorite.

Text.SourceString: I’m working on honing my urban photography skills this Spring.//I mean, as urban as it gets on Coral Island.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m working on honing my urban photography skills this Spring.//I mean, as urban as it gets on Coral Island.

Text.SourceString: I tried wearing sunglasses all the time because harsh light bothers me a lot.//But I can’t take good pictures that way.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried wearing sunglasses all the time because harsh light bothers me a lot.//But I can’t take good pictures that way.

Text.SourceString: I still get grumpy on super sunny days. I promise that’s not your fault! It’s worth it for the pics, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I still get grumpy on super sunny days. I promise that’s not your fault! It’s worth it for the pics, though.

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite hot drink?//I’m going to remember it. For reasons. Reasons related to imminent cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite hot drink?//I’m going to remember it. For reasons. Reasons related to imminent cold weather.

Text.SourceString: You’ve really made Coral Island a home for me. Thanks to you, I notice so many things I never did before.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ve really made Coral Island a home for me. Thanks to you, I notice so many things I never did before.

Text.SourceString: I thought I’d seen everything this island had to offer. I was wrong.//You opened my eyes!
Text.LocalizedString: I thought I’d seen everything this island had to offer. I was wrong.//You opened my eyes!

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to come up with a cute pet name for you. It has to be interesting! Nothing generic. Any ideas?
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to come up with a cute pet name for you. It has to be interesting! Nothing generic. Any ideas?

Text.SourceString: Are you hungry? I’m always hungry. I have a snack if you want one!
Text.LocalizedString: Are you hungry? I’m always hungry. I have a snack if you want one!

Text.SourceString: Wanna go out sometime? It’s so nice out.//<portrait=normal>We can go hiking! Or to the beach! Whatever you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Wanna go out sometime? It’s so nice out.//<portrait=normal>We can go hiking! Or to the beach! Whatever you want.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, you can get some really compelling shots in the rain. Other times, it’s just kinda drab.

Text.SourceString: Parting with Stephen that day at the beach was heart-wrenching...but I knew it was time to release him back to his world.
Text.LocalizedString: Parting with Stephen that day at the beach was heart-wrenching...but I knew it was time to release him back to his world.

Text.SourceString: But then, when he chose to stay! My heart swelled...everything just fell into place again.//<portrait=blushing>Thanks for being there for me, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: But then, when he chose to stay! My heart swelled...everything just fell into place again.//<portrait=blushing>Thanks for being there for me, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
